OL,3,C'I want to be proud': Why I'm finally
OL,4,Cshowing the world my scars
OL,6,FTriggered by skin trauma - such as
OL,7,Fsurgery, acne, or piercings - keloid
OL,8,Fscars are a result of an abnormal
OL,9,Fhealing response and excessive
OL,10,Fcollagen production.
OL,12,FBut unlike typical scars, they do not
OL,13,Ffade; instead, they can continue to
OL,14,Fexpand for months or even years.
OL,16,FKeloids are also significantly more
OL,17,Fcommon in pregnant women and people
OL,18,Fwith darker skin tones, including
OL,19,Fthose of African, Asian, or Latin-
OL,20,FAmerican descent.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
